A novel case of an adenomyosis-related uterine rupture in pregnancy. To date, few cases of uterine rupture related to adenomyosis have been reported. The current case report briefly describes a novel case of an adenomyosis related uterine rupture, while focusing on few symptoms that this kind of uterine rupture may have. Due to increasing rate of adenomyosis in Western countries, practicing obstetricians should carefully take in account silent uterine rupture related to adenomyosis.